{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875777504,"sessionID":"ses_2858f6ed1ffeJK9Yu7VH3Ei7mv","part":{"id":"prt_d7a71e3a7001hAox1GRAkRqyI6","messageID":"msg_d7a71096d001lHovWLt6imgoGG","sessionID":"ses_2858f6ed1ffeJK9Yu7VH3Ei7mv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ba228a1982ea40fc93f4ac88e17f8050","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec ŌĆö AR-024 DockerServiceÕ░üĶŻģ\n\nModule: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n## Purpose\n\nEncapsulate Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability check, build, info retrieval, push, and removal.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Docker client initialization\n\nThe system SHALL lazily initialize the Docker SDK client via `docker.from_env()` on first use.\n\n### Scenario: Client initialization is deferred\n- **GIVEN** a `DockerService` instance is created with `verbose=False`\n- **WHEN** no Docker operations are performed yet\n- **THEN** the internal `_client` field SHALL be `None`\n\n### Scenario: Client is obtained on first call\n- **GIVEN** `_get_client()` is called for the first time\n- **WHEN** the call executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL import `docker` lazily, call `docker.from_env()`, store the result in `self._client`, and return the client object\n\n### Scenario: Client reuse on subsequent calls\n- **GIVEN** `_get_client()` has been called at least once\n- **WHEN** `_get_client()` is called again\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the cached `_client` without re-initializing\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Docker availability check\n\nThe system SHALL provide `check_docker_available()` to verify Docker daemon connectivity.\n\n### Scenario: Docker is running and reachable\n- **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is running and accessible\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `docker.from_env().ping()` and return `True`\n\n### Scenario: Docker is not running or unreachable\n- **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is stopped or the socket is inaccessible\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch any exception and return `False`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image build\n\nThe system SHALL build container images from a Dockerfile with optional build arguments and streaming logs.\n\n### Scenario: Build with default parameters\n- **GIVEN** a valid `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, and `image_name`\n- **WHEN** `build_image()` is called with default `tag=\"latest\"` and `build_args=None`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `client.images.build(path=context_path, dockerfile=dockerfile_path, tag=\"{image_name}:latest\")`, compute `build_time` as elapsed seconds, and return `{\"image_name\", \"image_id\", \"image_size\", \"build_time\", \"tag\"}`\n\n### Scenario: Build with custom tag\n- **GIVEN** `tag=\"v1.2.3\"` is passed\n- **WHEN** `build_image()` runs\n- **THEN** the full tag SHALL be `{image_name}:v1.2.3`\n\n### Scenario: Build with proxy build arguments\n- **GIVEN** `build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"NO_PROXY\": \"localhost\"}`\n- **WHEN** the build is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass `buildargs` to `client.images.build()` so Docker receives the proxy configuration\n\n### Scenario: Verbose build logs streaming\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is passed to `build_image()`\n- **WHEN** the build runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL iterate over `build_logs` and print each `log[\"stream\"]` line (stripped) to stdout\n\n### Scenario: Build failure with verbose output\n- **GIVEN** `build_image()` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `verbose=True`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print `\"Build failed after {build_time:.1f}s: {e}\"` before raising\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image information retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve metadata (ID, size) for a built or pulled image.\n\n### Scenario: Get info for existing image\n- **GIVEN** an image `{image_name}:{tag}` exists locally\n- **WHEN** `get_image_info(image_name, tag)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `client.images.get(full_name)`, format size via `_format_size()`, and return `{\"image_id\", \"image_size\"}`\n\n### Scenario: Get info with default tag\n- **GIVEN** `get_image_info(image_name)` is called without tag\n- **WHEN** the lookup runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `tag=\"latest\"`\n\n### Scenario: Image not found\n- **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist locally\n- **WHEN** `get_image_info()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise the Docker SDK exception; if `verbose=True`, print `\"Error getting image info: {e}\"` before raising\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image size formatting helper\n\nThe system SHALL format byte counts as human-readable strings.\n\n### Scenario: Bytes under 1 KB\n- **GIVEN** `size_bytes < 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"{size_bytes} B\"`\n\n### Scenario: Kilobytes\n- **GIVEN** `1024 <= size_bytes < 1024 * 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size()` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"{size_bytes / 1024:.1f} KB\"`\n\n### Scenario: Megabytes\n- **GIVEN** `1024 * 1024 <= size_bytes < 1024 * 1024 * 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size()` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"{size_bytes / (1024 * 1024):.1f} MB\"`\n\n### Scenario: Gigabytes\n- **GIVEN** `size_bytes >= 1024 * 1024 * 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size()` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"{size_bytes / (1024 * 1024 * 1024):.1f} GB\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image push to registry\n\nThe system SHALL push images to a container registry with optional authentication.\n\n### Scenario: Push without registry URL\n- **GIVEN** `registry_url` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `push_image(image_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL push to `image_name` directly (assumes local registry or daemon-inferred target)\n\n### Scenario: Push with registry URL\n- **GIVEN** `registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"`\n- **WHEN** `push_image(image_name, registry_url)` runs\n- **THEN** the full image name SHALL be `\"registry.example.com/{image_name}\"`\n\n### Scenario: Push with authentication\n- **GIVEN** `username=\"user\"` and `password=\"pass\"` and `registry_url` are provided\n- **WHEN** `push_image()` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `client.login(username, password, registry=registry_url)` before pushing\n\n### Scenario: Push timing measurement\n- **GIVEN** a push completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the push finishes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"pushed_image\": full_image_name, \"push_time\": elapsed_seconds}`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image removal\n\nThe system SHALL remove local images with graceful failure handling.\n\n### Scenario: Successful removal\n- **GIVEN** the image `image_name` exists locally\n- **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `client.images.remove(image_name)` and return `True`\n\n### Scenario: Removal failure (image not found or in use)\n- **GIVEN** the image cannot be removed (e.g., in use by container)\n- **WHEN** `remove_image()` raises\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch the exception and return `False`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Legacy build wrapper\n\nThe system SHALL provide `build_image_legacy()` for backward compatibility with workspace/metadata-based builds.\n\n### Scenario: Legacy build with metadata defaults\n- **GIVEN** `workspace_path`, `metadata: AgentMetadata`\n- **WHEN** `build_image_legacy(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `dockerfile_path=workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"`, `context_path=workspace_path`, `image_name=metadata.agent_name`, `tag=metadata.version or \"latest\"`, and `build_args=None`\n\n### Scenario: Legacy build with explicit tag\n- **GIVEN** `tag=\"v2.0.0\"` is passed to `build_image_legacy()`\n- **WHEN** the build runs\n- **THEN** the tag SHALL be `\"v2.0.0\"` (overrides `metadata.version`)\n\n### Scenario: Legacy build inherits verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService` was constructed with `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** `build_image_legacy()` is called\n- **THEN** the `verbose` parameter passed to `build_image()` SHALL be `self.verbose`"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775875777494,"end":1775875777501}}}}
