{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875863679,"sessionID":"ses_2858f6ed1ffeJK9Yu7VH3Ei7mv","part":{"id":"prt_d7a733456001SLJ8t9sbLrdx0j","messageID":"msg_d7a7225c900171K0lqNVykCA5O","sessionID":"ses_2858f6ed1ffeJK9Yu7VH3Ei7mv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-1926f786fcc14b80a305e8cde602831b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-024 ŌĆö DockerService Õ░üĶŻģ\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEncapsulates Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability checking, building, information retrieval, registry push, and removal. The `DockerService` class provides a clean abstraction layer over the `docker` Python SDK, enabling CLI commands (`build`, `publish`) to manage container images without direct SDK coupling.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Docker client lazy initialization\n\nThe system SHALL lazily initialize the Docker client via `docker.from_env()` on first use, caching the client for subsequent operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Client deferred until first operation\n\n- **GIVEN** a `DockerService` instance is constructed with `verbose=False`\n- **WHEN** no Docker operations have been invoked yet\n- **THEN** the internal `_client` field SHALL be `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialized on first `_get_client` call\n\n- **GIVEN** `_client` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `_get_client()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Import the `docker` module lazily\n  - Call `docker.from_env()` to obtain a client\n  - Store the result in `self._client`\n  - Return the client object\n\n#### Scenario: Client reused on subsequent calls\n\n- **GIVEN** `_client` has been initialized previously\n- **WHEN** `_get_client()` is called again\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the cached `self._client` without re-initializing\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Docker availability check\n\nThe system SHALL provide `check_docker_available()` to verify Docker daemon connectivity.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker daemon running and responsive\n\n- **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is running and the socket is accessible\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Import `docker` and call `docker.from_env()`\n  - Invoke `client.ping()`\n  - Return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Docker daemon stopped or unreachable\n\n- **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is stopped or the socket is inaccessible\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch any exception and return `False`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image building\n\nThe system SHALL build container images from a Dockerfile with optional build arguments and verbose log streaming.\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with default parameters\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, and `image_name`\n- **WHEN** `build_image()` is called with default `tag=\"latest\"` and `build_args=None`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `client.images.build(path=context_path, dockerfile=dockerfile_path, tag=\"{image_name}:latest\")`\n  - Record `build_time` as elapsed seconds from start to completion\n  - Return `{\"image_name\", \"image_id\", \"image_size\", \"build_time\", \"tag\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with custom tag\n\n- **GIVEN** `tag=\"v1.2.3\"` is passed to `build_image()`\n- **WHEN** the build runs\n- **THEN** the full tag SHALL be `{image_name}:v1.2.3`\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with proxy build arguments\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"NO_PROXY\": \"localhost\"}`\n- **WHEN** `build_image()` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass `buildargs` to `client.images.build()` so Docker receives the proxy settings\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose build log streaming\n\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is passed to `build_image()`\n- **WHEN** the build runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL iterate over `build_logs` and print each `log[\"stream\"]` line (stripped) to stdout\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure with verbose output\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_image()` encounters an exception during the build\n- **WHEN** `verbose=True`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Record elapsed time as `build_time`\n  - Print `\"Build failed after {build_time:.1f}s: {e}\"` to stdout\n  - Raise the exception\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image information retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve metadata (ID, size) for a built or pulled image.\n\n#### Scenario: Get info for existing image with tag\n\n- **GIVEN** image `{image_name}:{tag}` exists locally\n- **WHEN** `get_image_info(image_name, tag)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `client.images.get(\"{image_name}:{tag}\")`\n  - Extract `image.id` and `image.attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)`\n  - Format size via `_format_size()`\n  - Return `{\"image_id\", \"image_size\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Get info with default tag\n\n- **GIVEN** `get_image_info(image_name)` is called without `tag`\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `tag=\"latest\"` as the default\n\n#### Scenario: Image not found\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist locally\n- **WHEN** `get_image_info()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Catch the Docker SDK exception\n  - If `self.verbose=True`, print `\"Error getting image info: {e}\"` to stdout\n  - Re-raise the exception\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image size formatting\n\nThe system SHALL format byte counts as human-readable strings.\n\n#### Scenario: Bytes under 1 KB\n\n- **GIVEN** `size_bytes < 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes B\"` (e.g., `\"512 B\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: Kilobytes (1 KB to 1 MB)\n\n- **GIVEN** `1024 <= size_bytes < 1024 * 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes / 1024:.1f KB\"` (e.g., `\"256.0 KB\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: Megabytes (1 MB to 1 GB)\n\n- **GIVEN** `1024 * 1024 <= size_bytes < 1024 * 1024 * 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes / (1024 * 1024):.1f MB\"` (e.g., `\"64.0 MB\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: Gigabytes (>= 1 GB)\n\n- **GIVEN** `size_bytes >= 1024 * 1024 * 1024`\n- **WHEN** `_format_size(size_bytes)` runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `\"size_bytes / (1024 * 1024 * 1024):.1f GB\"` (e.g., `\"2.5 GB\"`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image push to registry\n\nThe system SHALL push images to a container registry with optional authentication.\n\n#### Scenario: Push without registry URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `registry_url` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `push_image(image_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL push to `image_name` directly (assumes local registry or daemon-inferred target)\n\n#### Scenario: Push with registry URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"`\n- **WHEN** `push_image(image_name, registry_url)` runs\n- **THEN** the full image name SHALL be `\"registry.example.com/{image_name}\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Push with authentication\n\n- **GIVEN** `username=\"user\"`, `password=\"pass\"`, and `registry_url` are all provided\n- **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry_url)` before pushing\n\n#### Scenario: Push timing measurement\n\n- **GIVEN** a push operation completes\n- **WHEN** `push_image()` returns\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"pushed_image\": full_image_name, \"push_time\": elapsed_seconds}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image removal\n\nThe system SHALL remove local images with graceful failure handling.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful image removal\n\n- **GIVEN** image `image_name` exists locally and is not in use\n- **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `client.images.remove(image_name)`\n  - Return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Removal failure (image in use or not found)\n\n- **GIVEN** the image cannot be removed (e.g., in use by a container, or does not exist)\n- **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch the exception and return `False`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Legacy build wrapper\n\nThe system SHALL provide `build_image_legacy()` for backward compatibility with workspace/metadata-based builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Legacy build with metadata defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** `workspace_path`, `metadata: AgentMetadata`\n- **WHEN** `build_image_legacy(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use `dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"`\n  - Use `context_path = workspace_path`\n  - Use `image_name = metadata.agent_name`\n  - Use `tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"`\n  - Use `build_args = None`\n  - Call `build_image()` with the above parameters\n\n#### Scenario: Legacy build with explicit tag override\n\n- **GIVEN** `tag=\"v2.0.0\"` is passed to `build_image_legacy()`\n- **WHEN** the build executes\n- **THEN** the tag SHALL be `\"v2.0.0\"` (overrides `metadata.version`)\n\n#### Scenario: Legacy build inherits verbose setting\n\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService` was constructed with `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** `build_image_legacy()` is called without explicit `verbose`\n- **THEN** the `verbose` argument passed to `build_image()` SHALL be `self.verbose`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Constructor initialization\n\nThe system SHALL initialize `DockerService` with a verbose flag and uninitialized client.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with verbose flag\n\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)` is called\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Store `self.verbose = True`\n  - Initialize `self._client = None`\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor default verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| Default tag | `\"latest\"` | `docker_service.py` | Default image tag for builds and info retrieval |\n| Size thresholds | `1024`, `1024*1024`, `1024*1024*1024` | `docker_service.py` | Thresholds for size formatting (KB, MB, GB) |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python (client API) |\n| `time` | stdlib | Build/push timing measurement |\n| `pathlib.Path` | stdlib | Dockerfile and context path handling |\n| `typing` | stdlib | Type annotations (`Optional`, `Dict`, `Any`) |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | **existing** | Core DockerService implementation |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | uses | Consumes `DockerService.build_image()` for local builds |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | uses | Consumes `DockerService.push_image()` for registry push |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md`: DockerService API signature and field descriptions\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md`: Docker integration requirement scenarios\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `DockerService.__init__` stores `verbose` and initializes `_client=None`\n- [ ] `_get_client()` lazy-initializes via `docker.from_env()` and caches result\n- [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when daemon responds to ping\n- [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` on any exception\n- [ ] `build_image()` calls `client.images.build()` with correct parameters\n- [ ] `build_image()` returns `{image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time, tag}`\n- [ ] `build_image()` streams logs when `verbose=True`\n- [ ] `build_image()` prints failure timing when verbose and exception occurs\n- [ ] `build_image()` supports `build_args` for proxy configuration\n- [ ] `get_image_info()` returns `{image_id, image_size}` for existing image\n- [ ] `get_image_info()` uses `tag=\"latest\"` as default\n- [ ] `get_image_info()` prints error and re-raises when `verbose=True`\n- [ ] `_format_size()` formats bytes as B/KB/MB/GB correctly\n- [ ] `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry URL\n- [ ] `push_image()` calls `client.login()` when credentials provided\n- [ ] `push_image()` returns `{pushed_image, push_time}`\n- [ ] `remove_image()` returns `True` on success, `False` on failure\n- [ ] `build_image_legacy()` wraps `build_image()` with workspace/metadata defaults\n- [ ] `build_image_legacy()` uses `metadata.version or \"latest\"` as tag\n- [ ] `build_image_legacy()` inherits `self.verbose` setting"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875863645,"end":1775875863677}}}}
